#compdef oxfmt
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# oxc-project/oxc apps/oxfmt/src/cli/command.rs —
#   `FormatCommand` struct at lines 20-40 (the Bpaf-derived
#     top-level CLI struct with 4 external sub-parsers +
#     positional PATHs)
#   `Mode` enum + `mode()` parser combinator at lines 46-101
#     (5 variants, 4 cfg-gated on `feature = "napi"`)
#   `OutputMode` enum + `output_mode()` parser at lines
#     105-129 (3 variants: Write default | Check |
#     ListDifferent)
#   `ConfigOptions` at lines 145-152, `IgnoreOptions` at
#     155-164, `RuntimeOptions` at 168-175
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# oxfmt is the **Rust-native JavaScript/TypeScript formatter**
# from the oxc-project (the Rust JS toolchain that also
# includes oxlint, oxc_parser, etc.).  Drop-in replacement
# for Prettier with 10-50x performance.  Reads Prettier's
# config format and emits Prettier-equivalent output;
# supports migrating Prettier + Biome configs to oxfmt's
# native `.oxfmtrc.json`.
#
# Critical extraction note: oxfmt uses **bpaf** (NOT clap,
# argh, structopt, or maelstrom-macro) — **THE CORPUS'S
# FIRST DOCUMENTED BPAF-BASED CLI BINARY**.  bpaf is the
# 5th Rust CLI library documented in the corpus.  Quick
# comparison of the 5:
#   | Library | Style | Documented in |
#   |---|---|---|
#   | clap v4 | proc-macro derive + builder | many rounds |
#   | argh | proc-macro derive | R223 yofi |
#   | structopt | proc-macro derive (clap v3 predecessor) | R228 sntrup |
#   | bpaf | proc-macro derive + COMBINATOR API | R245 oxfmt |
#   | maelstrom-macro #[derive(Config)] | proc-macro for config+env+cli | R238 cargo-maelstrom |
# bpaf's unique selling point: **combinator API** —
# `bpaf::long("name").argument::<PathBuf>("PATH").hide_usage()`
# builds a parser programmatically (vs declaratively via
# derive attributes).  Used for the Mode parser at lines
# 65-101 because the variants depend on `cfg!(feature =
# "napi")` and need runtime combination via
# `bpaf::construct!([...])`.
#
# Critical extraction note: oxfmt's bpaf-derive attribute set
# documented:
#   `#[bpaf(options, version(VERSION))]`
#     — top-level annotation (= clap's `#[command(version)]`)
#   `#[bpaf(external)]`
#     — pulls in a sub-struct's bpaf-derived parser
#   `#[bpaf(external(name))]`
#     — pulls in a NAMED external parser function (vs the
#       struct-based external)
#   `#[bpaf(positional("PATH"), many, guard(fn, "msg"))]`
#     — positional with `many` (repeatable Vec) +
#       `guard(validate_fn, error_msg)` for validation
#   `#[bpaf(short, long, argument("VALUE"))]`
#     — flag with BOTH short + long + value argument
#   `#[bpaf(switch, hide_usage)]`
#     — boolean switch, HIDDEN from usage output (but still
#       parseable)
#   `#[bpaf(argument("VALUE"), many, hide_usage)]`
#     — value argument that's repeatable (Vec<>) + hidden
#
# Critical extraction note: oxfmt has **5 mode variants with
# 4 cfg-gated on `feature = "napi"`** at lines 46-63.  The
# napi feature is the Node.js / N-API integration; oxfmt's
# `--init`, `--migrate`, `--lsp`, `--stdin-filepath` modes
# all dispatch to JavaScript-side logic (presumably for
# Prettier-compatible behavior).  The default `Cli(Write)`
# mode is the only one that's always available.  Continues
# R233's feature-gating documentation by adding the
# **4-of-5 variant gating pattern** where the majority of an
# enum is feature-gated.
#
# Critical extraction note: `--migrate SOURCE` uses bpaf's
# **`argument::<String>("SOURCE").parse(|s| ...)` pattern**
# at lines 76-81 — a custom parser closure that accepts ONLY
# `prettier` or `biome` (case-insensitively via CowUtils'
# `cow_to_lowercase`) and returns a custom error for invalid
# values.  Documents bpaf's **parser-with-custom-validation**
# pattern — equivalent to clap's `value_parser = ...` closure
# but with explicit error message construction.
#
# Critical extraction note: `--write` / `--check` /
# `--list-different` form a **MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE output mode
# group** via `bpaf::construct!([write, check, list_different
# ]).group_help("Output Options:")` at line 128.  Default is
# `Write` (via `.fallback(Mode::Cli(OutputMode::Write))` at
# line 99).  This is the corpus's first documented bpaf
# `construct!([a, b, c])` mutex enum pattern.
#
# Critical extraction note: positional `PATH` arguments use
# `guard(validate_paths, PATHS_ERROR_MESSAGE)` at line 38 to
# REJECT paths containing `..` (parent directory traversal).
# Implemented at validate_paths() lines 10-16 using
# `Path::components()` + `Component::ParentDir`.  Security
# measure to prevent oxfmt from accidentally formatting
# files OUTSIDE the project root.  Documented in the
# completion description.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help and exit]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version and exit]' \
  '--init[(napi feature) initialize .oxfmtrc.json with default values]' \
  '--migrate=[(napi feature) migrate Prettier or Biome config to .oxfmtrc.json]:source:(prettier biome)' \
  '--lsp[(napi feature) start language server protocol server (for editor integration)]' \
  '--stdin-filepath=[(napi feature) read from stdin; use this filepath to infer parser]:path:_files' \
  '(--write --check --list-different)--write[format and write files in place (DEFAULT)]' \
  '(--write --check --list-different)--check[check if files are formatted; show statistics; exit non-zero if any need formatting]' \
  '(--write --check --list-different)--list-different[list files that would be changed]' \
  '(-c --config)'{-c+,--config=}'[config file path (.json/.jsonc/.ts/.mts/.cts/.js/.mjs/.cjs)]:file:_files -g "*.(json|jsonc|ts|mts|cts|js|mjs|cjs)"' \
  '--disable-nested-config[do not search for config files in subdirectories]' \
  \*'--ignore-path=[ignore file path (repeatable; default: .gitignore + .prettierignore in CWD)]:file:_files' \
  '--with-node-modules[format code in node_modules dir (SKIPPED by default)]' \
  '--no-error-on-unmatched-pattern[do not exit with error when pattern matches no files]' \
  '--threads=[number of threads to use (default: CPU count; set to 1 for single-threaded)]:n:' \
  '*:path or glob pattern (default: CWD; "!" prefix to exclude; ".." rejected for security):_files'
